**2.4.2 The \$10,000 Rule --- Mathematical Proof**

Analysis of 461 invoices reveals a **bimodal distribution** that proves
systematic financial engineering:

  ------------- -------------- ----------- -------------------- --------------------
  **Range**     **Invoices**   **% Total** **Interpretation**   **Money Flow**

  \$0 ---       3              0.7%        Small orders         Cash
  \$5,000                                                       

  **\$5,000 --- **162**        **35.6%**   **SPLIT trucks (2    **CASH --- flexible
  \$8,000**                                firms, each          money**
                                           \<\$10K)**           

  \$8,000 ---   3              0.7%        Near threshold       Cash (risky)
  \$9,000                                                       

  **\$9,000 --- **0**          **0.0%**    **DEAD ZONE ---      **N/A**
  \$12,000**                               nobody goes near     
                                           \$10K**              

  **\$15,000    **276**        **60.7%**   **FULL trucks (1     **BANK → credit
  ---                                      firm, \>\$10K)**     repayment**
  \$20,000**                                                    

  \$20,000+     10             2.2%        Large orders         Bank
  ------------- -------------- ----------- -------------------- --------------------

**Platform action:** Show real-time \$10K warning when entering firm
split. Calculate from weight × price. Decision remains manual
(Gadam/Agamyrat).

